    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> But then the filters values are not updated, which might leave the user with the \"no results and I don't know why\" UX...\n\nI really think those API calls are necessary to refresh the refinements list; even if we don't use the underlying hits -> nothing superfluous here I would say.\n\nI assume that in some very specific cases where you can ensure it will always return results, it could make sense but I don't have any in mind. For sure if it's to \"save\" API calls, we should not do it because the refinements refresh is as important as the hits refresh.\n",
